metadata.name: Tenebris #14
metadata.description:
Something stirs from the depths of shadow, not light, not darkness, but the breath between. Is there light within darkness? Or is darkness itself the meaning?

A study in silence and contrast. Where emptiness becomes form, and light exists only as the edge of shadow. "Tenebris" is not darkness itself, but the breath that lingers between presence and absence.

metadata.name: Automaton #269
metadata.description: An Elementary Cellular Automaton created with pure JavaScript. In this instance, the capability to invert the order of the rule has been added, and the drawing is performed from the bottom of the canvas to the top, resulting in a fresh perspective. Finally, a gradient is incorporated to accurately differentiate the states of the cells

metadata.name: Urban Jungle #147
metadata.description:
A riot of colors and shapes that blend urban art with natural elements. The trees and vibrant hues, seem to burst out of the concrete jungle, challenging the viewer's perception of the boundary between the city and nature. 

Elements are incorporated into the piece, adding to the overall sense of chaos and energy. Despite the seeming discordance, the composition is unified by the use of color and movement. 

"Urban Jungle" captures the raw and untamed spirit of the city, reminding us that even amidst the chaos, there is a kind of beauty to be found.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #665
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Reflejos #31
metadata.description:
Reflejos es un proyecto de arte generativo diseñado para existir en la blockchain de Tezos. Este proyecto se aloja en la plataforma fx(hash) y genera obras de arte únicas utilizando un algoritmo y un sistema numérico hexadecimal que se crea con cada nuevo token.

Este proyecto fue desarrollado utilizando la librería p5.js de JavaScript, creada por Lauren Lee McCarthy. Reflejos es el resultado de la interacción entre la percepción humana y un conjunto de reglas interpretadas por la máquina.

Inspirado por la experiencia de caminar junto al mar y los estados de calma y contemplación que esta actividad puede evocar, Reflejos busca entrelazar a los espectadores con las obras de la colección. 

La intención es motivar al espectador a explorar su interior y descubrir momentos de apertura perceptiva. 

El objetivo es que la obra provoque una sensación de calma y claridad en el espectador a través de una conexión íntima y personal.

metadata.name: Fractured Cells #9
metadata.description:
Poisson disc sampling of a noise field masked to a shape, and then Voronoi tessellation. Rendered in hand-drawn lines.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 48 curated possible palettes
- 4 possible color distribution methods
- 3 possible shapes: one circle, random circles, circles distributed based on a quadtree 
- 1 to 3 levels of polygon smoothing
- polygon outlines
- polygon fill density and direction
- hand-drawn line roughness

Rare features
- 1 circle
- no polygon smoothing
- background polygons offset from foreground
- color distribution to have a "striped" appearance

metadata.name: Skravert #193
metadata.description:
‘Skravert’ - Norwegian, verb, past tense. ‘The act of filling an area with lines; to shade an area’.

Skravert is a series of 320 sketches, each capturing the texture and feel of a material residing somewhere between cardboard and woolen rugs. The project is centred around rectangle subdivision and a line drawing algorithm, giving each piece its own unique expression when combined with a selection of 28 different color  palettes.  

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2021

metadata.name: Turbulence #134
metadata.description:
Swirly shapes are rendered by passes of poisson samples of a warped noise field. The noise shifts with each pass, creating a layered effect. 

Dense editions may take over 2 minutes to draw fully.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume at any time during the drawing.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a not 1:1 variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

Common:
- 43 set palettes plus many more with combinations
- 3 color distribution methods
- 50/50 dark
- 50/50 monochrome with bright highlights 
- 3 drawing styles: lines, points, colored pencils
- 5 noises effects: full screen, distance from center, distance from bottom, horizontal center, vertical center, random circles, 3,5, or 7 horizontal and vertical bars
- Poisson point distribution based on set layers or the noise value

Rare
- 15% chance of a dark monochrome with gold strands
